trans-unit.source:
\n

Gets the column number in the file that contains the code that is executing.
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxxx xxx xxxxxx xxxxxx xx xxx xxxx xxxx xxxxxxxx xxx xxxx xxxx xx xxxxxxxxx.

trans-unit.source:
This information is typically extracted from the debugging symbols for the executable.

\n
trans-unit.target: Xxxx xxxxxxxxxxx xx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxx xxxx xxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxxx xxx xxx xxxxxxxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

The file column number, or 0 (zero) if the file column number cannot be determined.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxx xxxx xxxxxx xxxxxx$ xx 0 $xxxx$ xx xxx xxxx xxxxxx xxxxxx xxxxxx xx xxxxxxxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

Gets the line number in the file that contains the code that is executing.
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxxx xxx xxxx xxxxxx xx xxx xxxx xxxx xxxxxxxx xxx xxxx xxxx xx xxxxxxxxx.

trans-unit.source:
This information is typically extracted from the debugging symbols for the executable.

\n
trans-unit.target: Xxxx xxxxxxxxxxx xx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxx xxxx xxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxxx xxx xxx xxxxxxxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

The file line number, or 0 (zero) if the file line number cannot be determined.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxx xxxx xxxx xxxxxx$ xx 0 $xxxx$ xx xxx xxxx xxxx xxxxxx xxxxxx xx xxxxxxxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

Gets the file name that contains the code that is executing.
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxxx xxx xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxxxxxx xxx xxxx xxxx xx xxxxxxxxx.

trans-unit.source:
This information is typically extracted from the debugging symbols for the executable.

\n
trans-unit.target: Xxxx xxxxxxxxxxx xx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxx xxxx xxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxxx xxx xxx xxxxxxxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

The file name, or null if the file name cannot be determined.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxx xxxx xxxx$ xx $xxxxxx$xxxx$$xxxxxx$ xx xxx xxxx xxxx xxxxxx xx xxxxxxxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

The offset from the start of the MSIL code for the method that is executing.

\n
trans-unit.target: $x$x$Xxx xxxxxx xxxx xxx xxxxx xx xxx XXXX xxxx xxx xxx xxxxxx xxxx xx xxxxxxxxx.$$x$$x

trans-unit.source:
\n

Gets the method in which the frame is executing.

\n

trans-unit.source:

The method in which the frame is executing.
